cpsc433

Interface SisyphusPredicates

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Environment

    public interface SisyphusPredicates
    This interface should be implemented by any class that reads Sisyphus I predicates. The implementing class should also extend the class PredicateReader.

    The method declarations here form the stubs you will need to implement all the predicates for the assignments. The static String definitions here don't need to be overridden: they will automatically work with PredicateReader to yield help information when the predicate "!help()" is interpreted.

    For more information on the semantics of these predicates, see the CPSC 433 W06 assignment specification.
